{"id":"quant-ph/0002020","submitter":"Shiro Kawbata","authors":"Shiro Kawabata (ETL, Japan)","title":"Quantum Interleaver: Quantum Error Correction for Burst Error","comments":"6 pages, 5 figures (RevTeX)","journal-ref":"J. Phys. Soc. Jpn. 69 (2000) 3540","doi":"10.1143/JPSJ.69.3540","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph cond-mat","license":null,"abstract":"  The concept of quantum interleaver and a simple method of quantum burst-error\ncorrection is proposed. By using the quantum interleaver, any quantum\nburst-errors that have occurred spread over the interleaved code word, so that\nwe can construct good quantum burst-error correcting codes without increasing\nthe redundancy of the code. We also discuss the general method of constructing\nthe quantum circuit for the quantum interleaver and the quantum network.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Feb 2000 13:59:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 9 Feb 2000 03:13:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 15 Feb 2000 12:20:24 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 27 Dec 2000 10:07:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-06"}
